Since 2002 the nonmedical use of opiate derivative prescriptions has constituted for over 70% of the total supply of “medically necessary” prescriptions due to doctor shopping, robbery, and even murder (Madras, 2010, p. 375). The U.S. has the highest proportion of 18 – 25 year olds in prison of any industrialized society in the world. This high proportion only accounts for drug related infractions and is causing considerable overcrowding and deteriorating conditions in the prison system (McBride, TerryMcElrath, Harwood, Inciardi, & Leukefeld, 2009, p. 74). This percentage does not mean however that only new generation people are becoming addicted to prescription drugs, because age groups are only used for statistics not addictions!

